(Original Requirements list)

Sprint -

Optional -
- Choose speed for level (Functional)
- Can have alternate versions of levels (Functional)
- Three different obstacles (Functional)
- Map difficulty selection (Functional)
- Different skins (Functional)
- Pause Button (Functional)

Mandatory -
- Game must have a score counter in endless mode (Functional)
- Game must handle character movement (Functional)
- Must reset when the player loses and restarts (Functional)


(Nick's Revised User Story Version of Requirements)
We determined all of our requirements are Functional requirements.

Optional -

- As a user, I want to be able to choose the speed for each level so that I can give myself more of a challenge if desired.

- As a user, I want alternate versions of levels in the level mode so that I can have more challenges to test my skills.

- As a administrator, I want three obstacles reusable obstacles so that they can be used like building blocks to build levels quicker.

- As a user, I want to be able to change the difficulty on each level so that If I'm having too many issues with a level I can make it easier to progress further.

- As a user, I want to be able to change how my avatar looks with skins so that I can customize my avatar to be my own.

- As a user, I want to be able to pause the game so that if things come up and I need to stop playing the game, I can come right back to where I was when I'm free.

Mandatory -

- As a user, I want to have a score counter in endless mode so that I can compete with others for a high score.

- As a user, I want to be able to control the avatar's movement, so that I can play the game.

- As a user, I level to be reset when I loose so that I can immediately try to beat the level again.
